Editorial: New blood at Metra

Put riders and taxpayers -- not the meddling politicians -- first

     * [127]print

     *
     *

   7:13 p.m. CDT, September 12, 2013

   For those of you keeping score at home: Two new Metra board members
   were approved this week, representing Kane and DuPage counties.
   Chicago's nominee awaits approval of the City Council. Two more members
   announced they'd be vacating their seats. Two other vacancies remain.

   A new commuter rail board is taking shape.

   New members, steel yourselves. This isn't a job for the faint of heart
   or weak of spine. The previous board -- including the handful of
   members still stubbornly rooted to their chairs -- has made a mess of
   things.
